To' the authority of scripture the Pharisees added that of tradition, and they accepted, under the name of traditions‚ several speculative tenets from the philosophy or religion of the eastern nations. The doctrines of fate or pre- destination, of angels and spirits, and of a future state of rewards and punishments, were in the number of these new articles of belief; and as the Pharisees, by the austerity of their manners, had drawn into their party the body of the Jewish people‚ the immor- tality of the soul became the prevailing sentiment of the synagogue, under the reign of the Asmonaean princes and pontiffs.
